   NOAA logo

   aer*on*o*my \a(e)r-'an-o-me\n [fr. Gk aero-] a branch of science that
   deals with the atmosphere of the Earth and the other planets with
   reference to their chemical composition, physical properties, relative
   motion, and responses to radiation from space.
   [bluebar.gif]
